dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi c Chibhabha b Chisoro 116 (121b 3x4 6x6 155m) SR: 95.86

dismissalComment.html: a fine knock comes to an end! Unselfish batting from Nabi. He was targeting the wide long-on boundary, looking for six, but it was a tired-looking shot and the bat turned in his hands as he played it. The ball still went very high in the air, but Chamu Chibhabha has a safe pair of hands in the outfield and he held it cleanly.

dismissalText.commentary: Noor Ali Zadran c Chisoro b Mutombodzi 60 (99b 5x4 0x6 125m) SR: 60.6

dismissalComment.html: this will peg them back a little! Noor Ali set himself for a slog sweep, but the ball was fuller and straighter than he was looking for and he completely lost his shape as he swung wildly to leg. The ball ballooned high off the top edge, and Chisoro sprinted to his left from mid on to set himself under the ball as it came down not far from the non-striker's end. It wasn't the easiest catch, but he clung on with both hands.

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Shahzad player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: this has gone miles up in the air! Shahzad wasn't trying anything too dramatic as he flicked to leg, but he played under a ball that rose on him and the top edge almost kissed the low cloud covering the ground before rocketing back down to earth, where Mutumbami was waiting to catch it.

dismissalText.commentary: Najibullah Zadran c Ervine b Masakadza 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: well held by Ervine! Najibullah slogged at this one angling across him, and the top edge looked like it might fall safely at short third man. But Ervine, who was at gully, nipped across at full speed and caught it on the run, over his shoulder. Afghanistan are stumbling a little now.

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Jongwe b Dawlat Zadran 46 (33b 7x4 1x6 57m) SR: 139.39

dismissalComment.html: fierce yorker! Jongwe wanted to drive through extra cover, but this fast, reverse swinging yorker zipped under his bat in a flash. Dawlat Zadran celebrates, and Afghanistan close in on a series-leveling win.

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine c & b Samiullah Shinwari 43 (58b 5x4 0x6 82m) SR: 74.13

dismissalComment.html: Ervine falls, Afghanistan are surging! Well, Shenwari's caught and bowled has saved his face. Ervine stepped down the track and hammered the ball straight back at him, and Shenwari stuck a hand up just in time. Somehow, the ball stuck, and the bowler set off in frenzied celebration towards fine leg.

an early wicket! Dawlat targeted Chibhabha with a short ball, and the batsman swiveled back to pull. But he couldn't get himself into position quickly enough, the ball skewing off the splice and looping tamely to the mid-on fielder.

Chigumbura departs! He'd not been able to find the boundary even once in this innings, and needed to hit out at every ball. dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c Noor Ali Zadran b Mohammad Nabi 35 (39b 1x4 3x6 52m) SR: 89.74

dismissalComment.html: he's played the shot well, but now it's brought about his downfall! Mutumbami swept hard at this one, but the ball bounced on him and a top edge looped to short fine leg. The fielder there had plenty of ground to cover, but timed his dive just right to hold the ball inches above the turf.

dismissalText.commentary: Tinotenda Mutombodzi c sub (Shafiqullah) b Amir Hamza 27 (50b 2x4 0x6 43m) SR: 54

dismissalComment.html: oh what a catch! Mutombodzi stepped back and lifted a drive inside out over extra cover, but couldn't get it quite square enough of the fielder running in from long off. It was Shafiqullah down there, I think, who is on as a sub fielder for Noor Ali. He had a lot of ground to cover, and had to dive too, but the ball stuck in his palm. Afghanistan snaffle another one!

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine c & b Samiullah Shinwari 43 (58b 5x4 0x6 82m) SR: 74.13

dismissalComment.html: Ervine falls, Afghanistan are surging! Well, Shenwari's caught and bowled has saved his face. Ervine stepped down the track and hammered the ball straight back at him, and Shenwari stuck a hand up just in time. Somehow, the ball stuck, and the bowler set off in frenzied celebration towards fine leg.

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza b Samiullah Shinwari 3 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: And there you go. Panic stations, everyone. He's bowled him! Shenwari has set off for the midwicket boundary, roaring in celebration, and Shahzad looks like he wants to smash the disturbed stumps down! Raza is slumped in the crease. He didn't read this one, that zipped straight on without spinning and also kept really low. Afghanistan are well on top now!

dismissalComment.html: and another! Zimbabwe are crumbling away. Aftab followed Dawlat's cue and fired down a fast yorker right at the batsman's toes. Masakadza swung right over the top of it, and his middle stump was knocked clear out of the ground.

dismissalText.commentary: John Nyumbu run out (Mohammad Nabi) 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: all done! Nyumbu slaps to point, but he doesn't want to run. Panyangara, however, does and keeps going even as his partner tries to send him back. Eventually Nyumbu decides he must go, but by then Aftab has the ball in his hands and he makes a mess of the stumps at the non-striker's end, rocketing a full strength throw at them from about half a foot away. An emphatic way to level the series!

commentPreTextItems.html: AYAZ KHAN: "The fat lady is going to sing any moment now "

commentTextItems.html: all done! Nyumbu slaps to point, but he doesn't want to run. Panyangara, however, does and keeps going even as his partner tries to send him back. Eventually Nyumbu decides he must go, but by then Aftab has the ball in his hands and he makes a mess of the stumps at the non-striker's end, rocketing a full strength throw at them from about half a foot away. An emphatic way to level the series!

commentPostTextItems.html: Unsurprisingly, Mohammad Nabi is Man of the Match for his knock - his first ton in ODIs. This series has come alive nicely today, and there will be renewed interest in the next match on Tuesday. Your commentator today has been Liam Brickhill, and I hope you've enjoyed my coverage. Look out for my match report in the next few minutes, and do join me again for the third game. Until then, goodbye!
imTurin: "it's really a major boost for Afgan Cricket.... I really want this team alongside with Ireland get some more crack with some major cricketing nations..... (y)"

4.55 pm This is more of what many expected from Afghanistan ahead of this series. Mohammad Nabi lead the way with his blazing hundred, which included six towering sixes, and then his team followed that up with a relentless display in the field. There was pace on the new ball, nagging lines and variations from the spinners even from 17-year old debutant legspinner Rashid Khan, and then a textbook display of reverse swing bowling by Dawlat Zadran at the death. Afghanistan have surged to a 58-run win, and it's 1-1 in the series!
Mohibullah Raza: "Here in Afghanistan every one is celebrating there win love you Afghan tigers"

commentTextItems.html: Panyangara backs away and hacks a length delivery through the covers without much timing.
tip-and-run single for Nyumbu, just behind point to get off the mark. Ironic cheers from the crowd.

dismissalText.commentary: Wellington Masakadza b Aftab Alam 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 20

commentTextItems.html: and another! Zimbabwe are crumbling away. Aftab followed Dawlat's cue and fired down a fast yorker right at the batsman's toes. Masakadza swung right over the top of it, and his middle stump was knocked clear out of the ground.

headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Salman Afghan: "big pressure on Jongwe now! now the rotation of strike will be an issue for Zim and he will not be able to strike every ball."

commentTextItems.html: a full toss on middle is punted down the ground, but just the one run. Afghanistan won't mind that, as it means Masakadza may well be on strike again in the next over.
squeezed out to point, right off the toe end as it left him late through the air
definite, late reverse swing for Dawlat, away from the left-hander. Again it's full and wide outside off, and again he can't lay bat to ball.

commentPreTextItems.html: Mid-on and mid-off are up for Masakadza.

commentTextItems.html: full and wide outside off, and Masakadza can't get close with a booming drive.

commentPreTextItems.html: Jongwe is practicing his heave to midwicket ... One feels he's got to face almost all of the strike if Zimbabwe are even to get close. Over 12 an over needed...

commentTextItems.html: a low full toss, on off stump, is slapped to mid-off.
Aftab fires down a bouncer, and Jongwe hooks it down to fine leg to keep the strike.

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: zimcricketforum: "Is Jongwe urging Chigumbura to start playing some shots? This strategy makes no sense." --- Bad time for bad form..

commentTextItems.html: Jongwe, meanwhile, is unfazed! Another length delivery is flapped up and over square leg, right into the gap, and away for four.

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c sub (Shafiqullah) b Aftab Alam 25 (54b 0x4 0x6 82m) SR: 46.29

commentTextItems.html: Chigumbura departs! He'd not been able to find the boundary even once in this innings, and needed to hit out at every ball. This was the ball to hit - a length delivery on middle and leg - but he picked out the fielder at deep midwicket. An off, off-colour innings. Though Jongwe remains, this should be the game in the bag for Afghanistan.

commentPreTextItems.html: Ajmal Khan: "What is Chig waiting for??"

commentTextItems.html: a yorker bounces off Jongwe's left foot and rolls to leg, and they charge through for a leg bye.
Jongwe finds the vital boundary! He was aiming for wide long on, but the ball curved in to him and flew off the inside half of the bat and down to long leg. They all count!

commentPreTextItems.html: HAMDARD Hamdull: "Chigumbura is more dangerous than we can think of him. He has issued the free license to Jongwe and he himself is staying calm in crease and giving Jongwe more confidence to enjoy his freedom. Afghanistan should fear Elton's strategy." ---- Still 74 off 36 looks too tall a task

commentTextItems.html: crunched out of the middle of the bat, but straight down to the long on fielder. In case you hadn't noticed, this is already Jongwe's highest score in internationals.
another slower ball. Chigumbura was winding up to have a full go, but checked his shot and slotted the ball into the covers instead.

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

commentTextItems.html: clubbed away to wide long on, but not out of the middle of the bat. The placement is such that they hurry back for the second.

commentPostTextItems.html: Fine leg is up now, and there's a cover sweeper.

commentTextItems.html: full toss once again, and Jongwe still can't get it past the man at cover. Just another single

with fine leg up, Chigumbura aims for a paddle sweep. But Dawlat sent down a slower ball that he didn't quite read, and he's struck on the pad. Outside off, by the looks of things, and they steal a single.

dismissalText.commentary: Tinotenda Mutombodzi c sub (Shafiqullah) b Amir Hamza 27 (50b 2x4 0x6 43m) SR: 54

dismissalComment.html: oh what a catch! Mutombodzi stepped back and lifted a drive inside out over extra cover, but couldn't get it quite square enough of the fielder running in from long off. It was Shafiqullah down there, I think, who is on as a sub fielder for Noor Ali. He had a lot of ground to cover, and had to dive too, but the ball stuck in his palm. Afghanistan snaffle another one!

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c sub (Shafiqullah) b Aftab Alam 25 (54b 0x4 0x6 82m) SR: 46.29

dismissalComment.html: Chigumbura departs! He'd not been able to find the boundary even once in this innings, and needed to hit out at every ball. This was the ball to hit - a length delivery on middle and leg - but he picked out the fielder at deep midwicket. An off, off-colour innings. Though Jongwe remains, this should be the game in the bag for Afghanistan.

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza b Samiullah Shinwari 3 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: And there you go. Panic stations, everyone. He's bowled him! Shenwari has set off for the midwicket boundary, roaring in celebration, and Shahzad looks like he wants to smash the disturbed stumps down! Raza is slumped in the crease. He didn't read this one, that zipped straight on without spinning and also kept really low. Afghanistan are well on top now!
